# Recursive Learning Platform Orientation

## Repository Structure
```
rl-platform/
├── clients/                 # Client-specific implementations
│   ├── bhb/                # BHB client
│   ├── elpl/               # ELPL client
│   ├── integral-ed/        # Integral Ed client
│   └── st/                 # StriveTogether client
│       ├── assets/         # ST-specific assets
│       │   ├── js/        # Client-specific JS
│       │   └── css/       # Client-specific CSS
│       ├── goalsetter.html # ST Goal Setter implementation
│       └── index.html      # Client landing page
├── shared/                 # Shared platform resources
│   ├── assets/            # Shared assets (images, CSS, JS)
│   └── templates/         # Shared HTML templates
└── index.html             # Platform landing page
```

## Key Files
- `shared/assets/js/chat.js` - Core chat functionality (shared)
- `clients/[client]/assets/js/[client]-[page]-auth.js` - Client-specific auth logic
- `shared/templates/chat-template.html` - Base chat template

## Current Focus
- ST Goal Setter implementation
- Path updates in goalsetter.html
- Client-specific auth logic

## Notes
- Client auth scripts are named for their specific pages (e.g., st-goalsetter-auth.js)
- Shared chat.js handles lambda calls to different assistants
- Each client maintains their own asset structure 